commitResults.messageTitle: Implement command echo and exit function
Implement command parsing and basic commands
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit introduces a new Parser class and implements basic commands.

Changes include:
- Add Parser class to read user input and handle Add,"bye" and List
- Implement ExitCommand to end chatbot on "bye" command
- Implement ListCommand to display tasks

These changes improves the structure by separating the logic for
handling user inputs and command classes for various actions. This will
allow for new actions to be easily added in the future.

The AddCommand, ExitCommand and ListCommand provides the basic chatbot
functionality
of adding tasks, exiting the program and displaying the tasklist.
- Update Command interface to use TaskList directly instead of generics

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor Fishman class to integrate parsing
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit refactors the Fishman class to use the new Parse class to
handle user inputs and execution of commands. This improves the overall
structure of the code.

Changes include:
- Integrate Parse for reading of command
- Simplify command execution flow
- Maintain separation of UI, Tasks and Commands

This changes allow for easier extensions in the future.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Ui class with task related display
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit updates the Ui class to display the newly added
command operations.

Changes include:
- Add displayAddedTask to echo task addition
- Add displayTaskList to show all tasks

This ensures proper integration and separation between the UI and
task operations.

commitResults.messageBody:
This will provide better clarity and guidance for others to better

This commit introduces the new MarkCommand class which implements
the mark/unmark functionality of fishman bot.

This changes provides the functionality required while allowing
future extensions to the mark feature.

- Implement MarkCommand to mark tasks as done or not done.
- Updated Parser to recognize "mark" and "unmark" commands.

This improves fishman bot functionality, allowing users to mark tasks
as complete or incomplete.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Deadline, Event and Todo Classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The classes are implemented to allow for the creation of new tasks
with attributes such as due dates, start and end times as well as tasks
without any specific timing.

This allows for further extensions according to future requirements.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update FishmanException to handle more exceptions
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit introduces EmptyListException, MissingArgumentException and
NumberFormatException.

EmptyListException manage cases where a task list is empty and
a mark/unmark command is issued. This ensures that the user receives an
error message when they attempt to mark/unmark tasks in an empty list.

MissingArgumentException checks and ensures that each command and the
respective information required is keyed in by the user. This ensures
that the user receives an error message when there is missing
information.

NumberFormatException manages cases where integer values are expected
but are not inputted by the user. This ensures that the user receives an
error message and can make amends to the command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Fishman and Parser to throw exceptions
commitResults.messageBody:
The Parser class will now throw exceptions according to the errors.

The Fishman class has been enhanced to throw an exception if there are
unexpected errors that are not already caught.

This improves error handling by ensuring that the commands/operations
on fishman bot are properly managed.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Parser,TaskList and Ui to handle deletion
commitResults.messageBody:
This commit updates Parser and TaskList class to contain logic for
deletion of task from the tasklist given the correct command.
This ensures that fishman bot is able to parse and execute the delete
command correctly.

The Ui class is updated to handle the display of task deletion, allowing
users to receive the appropriate feedback.

This commit adds IndexOutOfBoundsException to FishmanException to handle
cases when a provided index is out of bounds. This will display the
appropriate error message to the user.
